# How to provision an EC2 instance at amazonaws.com
AWS Console
EC2
Launch Instance
Choose Amazon Machine Image
Free Tier Linux Machine Image
t2.small, 2GB Memory
tag - Name $COMPUTER_NAME
$SECURITY_GROUP_NAME
Port Range 22 > Source > My IP
Add Rule > Port Range > 8080 > Source > Anywhere
Add Rule > Port Range > 8090 > Source > Anywhere
Add Rule > Port Range > 9000 > Source > Anywhere
Review and Launch
Create KeyPair or Use Existing Key Pair
Download KeyPair
Launch Instance

# at command line
chmod 400 $KEY_PAIR_NAME.pem
ssh -i "$KEY_PAIR_NAME.pem" $USERNAME@$DNSNAME.compute.amazonaws.com
sudo apt update
sudo apt full-upgrade -y
